The paper discusses the use of Evolutionary Algorithms (EAs) for dynamic optimization, which is a subfield of optimization and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of EAs for optimization, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of EAs for constructing a system to provide high-quality solutions efficiently in a dynamic environment, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
